The paper discusses a meta-modeling approach for automated hyper parameter optimization in computer vision algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a formalized meta-model for guiding algorithm development, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
